title: Sign in to your apprenticeship service account

heading_context: Sign in to your apprenticeship service account
chunks.html_content:
If you’re an employer, sign in to this service to:

  • create apprenticeship adverts
  • accept employer agreements with the Department for Education (DfE)
  • give account access to people within your organisation
  • give training providers permission to do some things for you (such as creating adverts and reserving funds)

You can also use this service to add details about your:

  • organisation or company
  • PAYE scheme
  • apprentices

If you do not pay the apprenticeship levy, use this service to reserve funding.

If you pay the levy, use this service to manage funding and provider payments.

There are different steps you need to follow to offer a trainee work experience.

heading_context: Sign in to your apprenticeship service account
chunks.html_content: You’ll need a GOV.UK One Login to set up or access an account. You can create one in the service using a work email address.

You can also contact the Apprenticeship service for advice.
